org.transitime.avl

Class AvlQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • java.util.concurrent.ArrayBlockingQueue<java.lang.Runnable>
          • org.transitime.avl.AvlQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Runnable>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Runnable>, java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue<java.lang.Runnable>, java.util.Queue<java.lang.Runnable>

    public class AvlQueue
extends java.util.concurrent.ArrayBlockingQueue<java.lang.Runnable>
    A queue of AvlClient runnables that can be used with a ThreadPoolExecutor. Implements by subclassing a ArrayBlockingQueue where the Runnable is an AvlClient. Also keeps track of the last AVL report per vehicle. When getting data form queue, if the data is obsolete (a new AVL report has been received for the vehicle) then that element from the queue is thrown out and the next item is retrieved until a non-obsolete one is found.

    Extended ArrayBlockingQueue class so that don't have to create a blocking queue from scratch.

    Note: wanted to extend from ArrayBlockingQueue but that didn't work for the ThreadPoolExecutor which expects a BlockingQueue. So had to resort to doing ugly casts.

    Author:
    SkiBu Smith
